
'''= RP2P: "Sharing mediated by relational responsibility, where your response-ability matters".'''

=Discussion=

Tim Adalin:

"A key motivating intent here is to see whether effective and vital contexts and rhythms exist between, and distinct from, private communication held inside a membrane, and open source communication--especially when it tends to a form of broadcast associated with algorithmically tuned attention hacking, and passive, faux-relational consumerism found on dominant social sharing platforms today.

From another angle, this is a contribution to the space between networks in an ecology of networks, for the purpose of sharing value to each of those networks, as well as travellers in search of resonant channels of others."
